The paper deals with an online optimization problem involving the knapsack problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and operations research. The paper proposes randomized algorithms for the problem, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.GT (computational game theory), cs.IT (information theory), cs.LG (machine learning), or cs.AI (artificial intelligence).
